template: Generate one single-sentence plain-English prompt describing a realistic software engineering task in {technical_domain} that includes defining requirements, building components, testing, fixing issues, and deploying to an environment; output only the prompt text under 45 words.
filled_prompt: Generate one single-sentence plain-English prompt describing a realistic software engineering task in mobile app that includes defining requirements, building components, testing, fixing issues, and deploying to an environment; output only the prompt text under 45 words.

message.content: Build a notification system for the app by defining specs, coding UI and logic, running tests, debugging failures, and releasing to the staging server.
message.reasoning_content:
Hmm, the user wants a concise prompt for a mobile app engineering task covering the full lifecycle. Let me break down the requirements: it needs to include requirements definition, component building, testing, bug fixing, and deployment, all in one sentence under 45 words.

Okay, mobile app development... realistic scenario... maybe focus on a common feature like notifications. That touches multiple areas: defining how notifications work, building the UI and backend, testing, fixing bugs, and deploying. 

Keep it simple and action-oriented. Start with the core task, then list the key phases without being too technical. Need to ensure all five elements are covered naturally. 

How about: "Build a notification system for the app by defining specs, coding UI and logic, running tests, debugging failures, and releasing to the staging server." Yes, that hits all points and stays under the word limit.
